======================
USBUART Click Board
======================

USB UART Click is an accessory board in mikroBUS form  
factor. It is a compact and easy solution for adding serial  
UART communication via USB cable.

=================
Key features
=================
* Configurable CBUS I/0 pins and entire USB protocol handled on the chip.
* 128 bytes long receive buffer
* 256 bytes long transmit buffer

==================
INTERFACE SETTINGS
==================
The MCU connects to the serial port of the USB-UART click board with the following parameters:

* Baud rate: 9600
* Data bits: 8
* Parity: None
* Stop bits: 1
* Voltage: 3.3V

Interrupts: Only if drivers configured to use IRQs. 


====================
CLICK BOARD EXAMPLE 
====================

Example performs the simple read and write operations through Asynchronous Mode
of operation.


====================
RUNNING THE EXAMPLE 
====================

#. Add USB-UART click component to application
#. Configure dependencies, check default driver assignment 

- USART: Add to run example, assign relevant pins. Ensure printf support is selected.
- NOTE: Incase the Click supports only 5v Supply, make sure that it is provided Externally.

3. Configure system drivers

- Enable global interrupts if configured any drivers to use IRQ.

4. Export Project: Name and download to relevant IDE.
5. In Atmel Studio 7: File->Import->Atmel Start Project.
6. In main.c

- In main, while(1) loop call: USBUART_example()(./examples/src/click_example.c)
- Add related headerfile: #include<click_example.h>(./examples/include/click_example.h)

7. Build and flash into supported evaluation board.
8. Responses from the module are stored in corresponding variables. If required, verify the data using standard debug methods.
